message: "If you use this repository in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Structural Feasibility Confidence (SFC): From Engineering Confidence to Structural Feasibility Metrics and the Structural Boundaries of LLMs"
authors:
  - family-names: Tan
    given-names: Sizhe
    affiliation: Independent Researcher
abstract: "Structural Feasibility Confidence (SFC) proposes structural feasibility as a foundational engineering principle connecting human engineering confidence, feasibility metrics, Large Language Model behavior, and future Structural Intelligence architectures. The repository develops SFC through three stages: Structural Feasibility Confidence, Structural Feasibility Metrics, and Structural Feasibility Scope. It argues that many capabilities of modern LLMs can be interpreted as implicit structural feasibility evaluation, while the Structural Feasibility Scope Principle (SFSP) clarifies the architectural boundary between implicit feasibility computation and systems requiring explicit structural representations, runtime state, structural memory, task graphs, differential structures, and persistent internal representations."
keywords:
